WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.230
Now let us use particles to explain why solids, liquids,
and gases behave so differently.

2
00:00:06.230 --> 00:00:12.838
A solid keeps its shape. A metal spoon does not slowly
pour off the table, which is helpful for lunch.

3
00:00:12.838 --> 00:00:20.909
In a simple particle model, solid particles are close
together and arranged in a pattern. They vibrate, but they
do not wander around the room.

4
00:00:20.909 --> 00:00:28.110
A liquid keeps its volume but changes shape. Water sits in
a glass, then takes the shape of the glass.

5
00:00:28.110 --> 00:00:34.139
In the particle model, liquid particles are still close
together, but they can slide past each other.

6
00:00:34.139 --> 00:00:42.057
A gas spreads out. Air fills a balloon. Take away the
balloon and the gas does not stay in a neat balloon-shaped
lump.

7
00:00:42.057 --> 00:00:47.472
The model explains why solids hold shape, liquids flow,
and gases fill containers.

8
00:00:47.472 --> 00:00:57.270
Heating gives particles more energy. In a solid, enough
heating can let particles move out of fixed positions.
That is melting: solid to liquid.

9
00:00:57.270 --> 00:01:06.825
Cooling removes energy. A liquid can slow down until its
particles settle into a solid pattern. That is freezing:
liquid to solid.

10
00:01:06.825 --> 00:01:16.324
Evaporation is liquid to gas. It can happen at the surface
even without boiling. A wet towel drying is water
particles escaping into the air.

11
00:01:16.324 --> 00:01:24.552
Condensation is gas to liquid. Water vapour meets a cold
surface, slows down, and becomes tiny droplets.

12
00:01:24.552 --> 00:01:36.849
Use the model to predict. If particles are close and
locked into a pattern, the substance keeps its shape. If
they are close but sliding, it flows. If they are far

13
00:01:36.849 --> 00:01:44.744
That is why a balloon gets bigger when you blow air into
it. You are adding gas particles, and they push out into
the space available.

14
00:01:44.744 --> 00:01:54.801
It is also why a puddle slowly dries. The water is not
being deleted. Some particles at the surface have enough
energy to escape into the air.

15
00:01:54.801 --> 00:02:09.024
